Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, core,
and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips. Drain and rinse
@black beans{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Finely dice @tomato{1}.
Quarter @lime{1}.

== Rojo Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add scallion whites; cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant and translucent,
~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and half the
@tomato paste{1.5%oz}. Cook, stirring, until rice is evenly coated,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Add 1 cup water (2 cups for 4), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 1 tsp
@southwest spice blend{1%tbsp} (2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{}. (You'll
use the rest of the Southwest Spice later.) Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce heat to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Turn
off heat and keep covered until ready to serve.

== Black Bean & Pepper Filling ==

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add green pepper; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with
salt and @pepper{}.

Add beans, @tex-mex paste{1}, remaining @southwest spice blend{}, and 1/4 cup
water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until filling is combined and
thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Creamy Cilantro Sauce & Pico de Gallo ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @vegan mayo{4%tbsp}, cilantro, and a pinch of salt
and pepper. Add water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling
consistency.

In a separate small bowl, combine tomato, scallion greens, and a squeeze of
lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and
microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Lay tortillas on a clean work surface. Add as much rice, bean filling, and pico
de gallo as you like across the bottom third of tortillas. Drizzle with as much
sauce as you like.

Fold bottom edge of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right
sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to
form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates along with any remaining beans,
remaining rice, and remaining pico de gallo. Serve with any remaining sauce for
dipping and remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Fresh, healthy, and filling in 30 minutes–vamanos!